The Pejuola community in Idi-Aba, Abeokuta, Ogun State, has expressed support for Governor Dapo Abiodun’s decision to empower the state’s youths and develop the state. The new Baale of the community, Chief Taiwo Ekerin (Ilufemiloye 1), stated this during his investiture and appointment of members of Baale-in-Council at Oke-Lantoro in Abeokuta. In a statement by his spokesperson, Mr Passover Adeshina, after the event on Sunday, Baale Ekerin noted that Abiodun needed the support of all indigenes, both home and abroad, to move the state forward through job creation, youth empowerment, education and health care delivery. 